00:38:25.950 --> 00:38:28.720
So the question was,
what happens with,

00:38:28.720 --> 00:38:29.600
say, Hurricane Sandy?

00:38:29.600 --> 00:38:31.550
Once you happen to be named
Sandy and a hurricane comes

00:38:31.550 --> 00:38:32.390
through that--

00:38:32.390 --> 00:38:33.950
this is true for Katrina
as well.

00:38:33.950 --> 00:38:36.020
There are negative externalities
there, that it's

00:38:36.020 --> 00:38:39.230
horrible to be named after
something that was a tragedy.

00:38:39.230 --> 00:38:42.700
So one argument there is maybe
what we should do is pick a

00:38:42.700 --> 00:38:47.070
name that's uncommon but with
a letter that's very common.

00:38:47.070 --> 00:38:50.860
So since most of the research
focuses on the letters rather

00:38:50.860 --> 00:38:53.250
than the names, maybe we should
pick the least common

00:38:53.250 --> 00:38:55.610
name with the letter
that's most common.

00:38:55.610 --> 00:38:56.660
That's one answer.

00:38:56.660 --> 00:38:57.140
But you're right.

00:38:57.140 --> 00:38:59.440
There are always questions like
that that we should be

00:38:59.440 --> 00:39:01.050
juggling and throwing
into the mix.

00:39:01.050 --> 00:39:03.040
It's not obvious that there
are no externalities.

00:39:03.040 --> 00:39:05.640
But I think in general in a
lot of these cases, these

00:39:05.640 --> 00:39:07.480
interventions are
so inexpensive.

00:39:07.480 --> 00:39:10.830
Another one is in Glasgow,
Scotland, and in parts of

00:39:10.830 --> 00:39:13.480
Japan, they've shown blue lights
on certain parts of

00:39:13.480 --> 00:39:16.820
town that reminded people
presumably of police and of

00:39:16.820 --> 00:39:19.700
being watched, so they behaved
much more honestly.

00:39:19.700 --> 00:39:20.990
The same is true with
billboards.

00:39:20.990 --> 00:39:23.900
If you put up a billboard with
eyes, a pair of human eyes,

00:39:23.900 --> 00:39:25.140
that costs very little.

00:39:25.140 --> 00:39:27.530
But it has the effect of
making people feel like

00:39:27.530 --> 00:39:28.600
they're being watched.

00:39:28.600 --> 00:39:30.640
And there's good evidence to
suggest that they are much

00:39:30.640 --> 00:39:32.790
more likely to behave honestly
when there's a billboard with

00:39:32.790 --> 00:39:33.900
eyes around.

00:39:33.900 --> 00:39:34.980
The same is true
with a mirror.

00:39:34.980 --> 00:39:37.030
If you happen to open a
cupboard-- if you have a

00:39:37.030 --> 00:39:38.590
cupboard with all your
chocolates, and you're trying

00:39:38.590 --> 00:39:41.310
to keep to a diet, put a mirror
up, because every time

00:39:41.310 --> 00:39:44.680
you open it, you'll be staring
into your soul as you reach in

00:39:44.680 --> 00:39:46.310
and try to grab the food
that you're not

00:39:46.310 --> 00:39:47.430
supposed to be eating.

00:39:47.430 --> 00:39:48.170
So you're right.

00:39:48.170 --> 00:39:50.560
There are some externalities
and some negatives.

00:39:50.560 --> 00:39:52.940
But generally speaking, I think
the positives greatly

00:39:52.940 --> 00:39:55.850
outweigh the negatives.

