hospital example, how do you

00:40:00.485 --> 00:40:02.870
know that it's a difference
between a beautiful and not

00:40:02.870 --> 00:40:03.367
beautiful view?

00:40:03.367 --> 00:40:06.349
So for instance, what if you
were looking at a skyline view

00:40:06.349 --> 00:40:08.834
that was beautiful and
had shrubbery?

00:40:08.834 --> 00:40:10.822
How do you know it's nature
and not just beautiful

00:40:10.822 --> 00:40:12.820
[INAUDIBLE]?

00:40:12.820 --> 00:40:13.240
ADAM ALTER: You're right.

00:40:13.240 --> 00:40:13.450
Yeah.

00:40:13.450 --> 00:40:15.330
So it could be-- the question
was, how do we know that it's

00:40:15.330 --> 00:40:16.240
not just beauty?

00:40:16.240 --> 00:40:18.300
How do we know that it's not
just that one view is nicer

00:40:18.300 --> 00:40:19.230
than the other?

00:40:19.230 --> 00:40:21.850
Like what if you had a really
ugly natural view or a really

00:40:21.850 --> 00:40:25.100
pretty view that's sculpted,
but it's concrete?

00:40:25.100 --> 00:40:26.390
And that's a great question.

00:40:26.390 --> 00:40:29.080
And it's not something you can
address without study.

00:40:29.080 --> 00:40:31.430
But a lot of other studies
ask the same question.

00:40:31.430 --> 00:40:33.730
So in one study, people watched
the most horrific

00:40:33.730 --> 00:40:36.300
video you can imagine
of animals being

00:40:36.300 --> 00:40:37.800
put through an abattoir.

00:40:37.800 --> 00:40:40.670
It's a very distressing video,
and it's a propagandist video

00:40:40.670 --> 00:40:43.920
that tries to get people to
eat less meet, obviously.

00:40:43.920 --> 00:40:44.940
And they watched this video.

00:40:44.940 --> 00:40:47.950
And when they then performed
various mental tasks, they did

00:40:47.950 --> 00:40:50.140
much worse on the task,
as you'd expect.

00:40:50.140 --> 00:40:53.190
They were distracted and
a little bit disturbed.

00:40:53.190 --> 00:40:56.570
And what they did with other
people was they got them to

00:40:56.570 --> 00:40:58.680
walk through a beautiful natural
environment or a

00:40:58.680 --> 00:41:01.010
beautiful environment or a very
nice environment that

00:41:01.010 --> 00:41:02.130
wasn't natural.

00:41:02.130 --> 00:41:03.890
And they found in that
experiment, even though the

00:41:03.890 --> 00:41:07.720
beauty of the two environments
was rated equally highly, that

00:41:07.720 --> 00:41:10.510
only the natural environment
had this positive effect.

00:41:10.510 --> 00:41:12.720
And one of the arguments is that
one of the things that

00:41:12.720 --> 00:41:14.610
distinguishes a natural
environment from a built

00:41:14.610 --> 00:41:16.870
environment, even if it's
beautiful, is that a built

00:41:16.870 --> 00:41:18.390
environment is static.

00:41:18.390 --> 00:41:20.320
A natural environment, you
have the rustle of wind

00:41:20.320 --> 00:41:20.970
through leaves.

00:41:20.970 --> 00:41:22.760
You have the movement
of a river.

00:41:22.760 --> 00:41:24.150
All of that stuff is critical.

00:41:24.150 --> 00:41:26.530
And William James was one of
the first and greatest

00:41:26.530 --> 00:41:28.350
philosophers and
psychologists--

00:41:28.350 --> 00:41:29.850
not the first philosopher,
but one of the first

00:41:29.850 --> 00:41:31.290
psychologists--

00:41:31.290 --> 00:41:32.940
he talked about two kinds
of attention.

00:41:32.940 --> 00:41:35.490
And one of his arguments was
that it's this kind of stuff

00:41:35.490 --> 00:41:37.950
that visits on you that you
don't have to deal with.

00:41:37.950 --> 00:41:42.010
You don't have to dodge cars or
remember things, that your

00:41:42.010 --> 00:41:44.690
attention is grabbed by nature
and the movement of the wind

00:41:44.690 --> 00:41:46.400
through the trees and
all that stuff.

00:41:46.400 --> 00:41:49.470
That's a replenishing kind of
attention, whereas it's very

00:41:49.470 --> 00:41:52.070
stressful to have to deal with
the movement of cars and

00:41:52.070 --> 00:41:54.310
dodging traffic and all the
stuff that we normally

00:41:54.310 --> 00:41:55.710
associate with stress.

00:41:55.710 --> 00:41:58.680
So there's something about the
kind of attention that is

00:41:58.680 --> 00:42:01.150
drawn out of you from natural
environments that has this

00:42:01.150 --> 00:42:03.110
effect beyond just beautiful

00:42:03.110 --> 00:42:06.620
environments that aren't natural.

00:42:06.620 --> 00:42:07.030
Yeah.

00:42:07.030 --> 00:42:08.914
